An Ebute-Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court yesterday remanded in prison Charles Amakanyadioha, 52, and Raphel Amaechi, 52, following their arraignment for alleged kidnapping of three children. Chief Magistrate Adeola Adedayo made the order after Amakanyadioha and Amaechi pleaded not guilty. Mrs Adedayo adjourned till June 25. Prosecuting Inspector Chinalu Uwadione said the defendants committed the offence around 1:40pm on June 14 at Gboke Street, Ijagemo in Ikorodu, Lagos. Uwadione said the kidnapped children’s ages were two, four and six.